02:13.866 --> 02:16.166
- [DOOR SLAMS]
- Benny, what are you doing out here?

02:16.168 --> 02:18.271
Oh, hey, Dad. Mom needs you.

02:19.104 --> 02:20.472
How long have
you been listening?

02:21.240 --> 02:22.242
I, uh...

02:23.508 --> 02:25.644
Listen, buddy, you don't need
to hear this.

02:26.412 --> 02:27.713
It's grown-up stuff, okay?

02:28.781 --> 02:30.516
Okay, Dad. It's cool though.

02:30.782 --> 02:32.582
I'm not scared of monsters
anymore.

02:32.584 --> 02:35.153
Oh, I forgot you're ten now,
you can't be scared.

02:35.387 --> 02:37.488
- Nope.
- Okay, go tell Mom I'll be down

02:37.490 --> 02:38.856
- in a minute, okay?
- Okay, Dad.

02:38.858 --> 02:39.893
All right.

02:43.194 --> 02:46.465
JACOB ON RECORDING: <i>Death
is everywhere. No one is immun.</i>

02:50.902 --> 02:52.371
<i>It will infect us all.</i>

03:01.747 --> 03:05.318
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

03:06.651 --> 03:12.191
- [GROWLING]
- [MUFFLED VOICES]

03:22.334 --> 03:23.969
- DAVID: Oh, nice!
- [CLAPPING]

03:24.637 --> 03:26.338
All right, Benny, dude,
you're up.

03:26.806 --> 03:28.739
- Oh, this is gonna be tough.
- Okay. Yeah.

03:28.741 --> 03:30.573
You know, I'm gonna help
you focus here.

03:30.575 --> 03:32.644
- Oh, yeah, that's helping me?
- Mm-hmm.

03:34.947 --> 03:37.883
- [ALL] Oh!
- [CASSIE LAUGHING]

03:38.550 --> 03:40.887
Okay, guys, game over.
You know what that means, right?

03:41.354 --> 03:42.388
Bedtime.

03:44.824 --> 03:47.427
But I'm not even tired!

03:54.834 --> 03:55.968
[KISSING]

03:57.436 --> 03:58.438
Goodnight.

04:02.841 --> 04:04.777
- Goodnight, dude.
- Goodnight.

04:06.245 --> 04:08.281
- You okay, buddy?
- Yeah.

04:10.383 --> 04:11.618
What you saw earlier...

04:12.751 --> 04:13.951
forget about it, okay?

04:14.853 --> 04:18.456
Part of my job is to help people
with the things they make up.

04:19.257 --> 04:21.360
- You understand?
- I get it, Dad.

04:21.793 --> 04:22.961
It's like your comic books.

04:24.262 --> 04:25.397
It's all make-believe.

04:26.499 --> 04:27.400
Got it.

04:30.002 --> 04:31.937
- DAVID: Love you, buddy.
- Love you too.

04:37.442 --> 04:38.810
You let him in your office?

04:41.646 --> 04:44.783
No, he just, um, peeked in
for a second, that's all.

04:45.451 --> 04:47.020
A second is all it takes, David.

04:49.387 --> 04:51.790
You're right. I'm sorry.

04:53.492 --> 04:56.629
It's okay, just keep the door
locked from now on, okay?

04:57.262 --> 04:58.663
I will. I...

04:59.665 --> 05:02.001
I've just been pounding my brain
over this one.

05:04.302 --> 05:05.737
Oh, sweetie, uh, I know, I...

05:07.305 --> 05:08.307
I can tell.

05:10.309 --> 05:11.511
You'll figure it out.

05:12.778 --> 05:16.449
You always do and that's why
I love you...

05:17.382 --> 05:18.651
Dr. Warren.

05:20.552 --> 05:21.821
I got to go clean up.

05:31.329 --> 05:33.098
[MOANS] Okay.

05:34.298 --> 05:36.001
Don't keep me waiting, okay.

05:55.086 --> 05:56.389
[CASSIE SIGHS]

06:35.528 --> 06:36.528
[DOOR CREAKS]

06:37.862 --> 06:39.064
BEN: What are you doing?

06:39.665 --> 06:41.934
I heard scary noises in my room.

06:43.067 --> 06:45.137
- What are you looking at?
- Nothing.

06:45.704 --> 06:48.441
- You can't look at this.
- Come on, I wanna see.

06:52.076 --> 06:55.814
Nobody knows where it comes from
but it's always there...

06:56.716 --> 06:58.117
watching over while you sleep.

06:58.916 --> 07:02.454
Waiting for you to open
your eyes for the last time.

07:06.891 --> 07:08.159
It stalks its prey.

07:08.793 --> 07:11.729
It hides and watches you
without you even knowing.

07:12.630 --> 07:16.067
It waits for the perfect moment
when you're least expecting.

07:17.036 --> 07:18.704
It's got one hooked claw

07:19.170 --> 07:21.706
and the other hand has nails
so big

07:22.007 --> 07:24.209
- they look like butcher knives!
- Stop!

07:25.110 --> 07:27.713
You're such a baby.
Do you want me to stop?

07:28.014 --> 07:31.617
You're scaring me.
I don't like this story.

07:32.951 --> 07:34.953
Okay fine, I'll stop.

07:35.420 --> 07:37.122
I told you were too young
for this stuff.

07:46.197 --> 07:47.532
[THUDS]

07:50.836 --> 07:52.939
Oh. Ben?

07:55.074 --> 07:56.542
You gotta be kidding me.

07:57.675 --> 07:58.944
[SIGHS]

08:01.846 --> 08:02.948
Seriously.

08:06.617 --> 08:07.620
[CASSIE GRUNTS]

08:08.521 --> 08:10.223
- [GRUNTS]
- [CASSIE PANTS]

08:11.122 --> 08:13.692
CASSIE: David! [GRUNTS]

08:22.901 --> 08:24.002
David!

08:25.603 --> 08:27.973
JACOB ON RECORDING: <i>It's here,
it's always here.</i>

08:29.975 --> 08:34.647
- [CRIES] David!
- What was that?

08:46.892 --> 08:48.861
CASSIE: Stay back! [CRIES]

08:49.595 --> 08:51.898
[CASSIE PANTING]
Go to your room!

08:55.835 --> 08:58.235
JACOB ON RECORDING: <i>The Rake is
a disease that needs no motive,</i>

08:58.703 --> 08:59.869
<i>once you give in...</i>

08:59.871 --> 09:01.606
- [PANTING]
- BEN: What's going on?

09:14.852 --> 09:16.585
- Listen to me. Listen to me.
- ASHLEY: Mommy.

09:16.587 --> 09:18.789
You have to stay here, okay?
Be very quiet.

09:18.791 --> 09:20.156
- I'm going to get help.
- ASHLEY: Mommy.

09:20.158 --> 09:22.861
Just be quiet, okay? Okay? Okay?

09:25.798 --> 09:27.832
[CASSIE WHISPERS] Okay?
Stay quiet, okay?

09:28.600 --> 09:29.969
- I love you.
- BEN: Mom?

09:35.573 --> 09:39.878
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]
- [DOOR KNOB RATTLING]

09:41.279 --> 09:43.814
- [THUDS]
- [CASSIE GRUNTS]

09:44.282 --> 09:46.185
[CASSIE PANTING]

09:48.254 --> 09:50.089
David! David!

09:53.192 --> 09:54.192
CASSIE: David!

09:54.625 --> 09:55.993
JACOB ON RECORDING:
<i>...traumatizing but...</i>

09:55.995 --> 09:58.798
- [BANGING ON DOOR]
- <i>...what came out of her...</i>

10:02.967 --> 10:05.170
[CASSIE CRIES]

10:07.706 --> 10:08.807
[KNIFE TEARS]

10:18.716 --> 10:19.985
[SIGHS]

10:28.159 --> 10:31.795
In conclusion, Jacob's obsession
with the Rake could be seen

10:31.797 --> 10:34.667
as a supernatural hallucination.

10:42.041 --> 10:43.042
DAVID: Cassie!

10:46.077 --> 10:47.646
[GASPS]

10:58.323 --> 10:59.924
[DOOR CREAKS]

11:08.966 --> 11:10.436
JACOB ON RECORDING:
<i>Beyond compare...</i>

11:13.371 --> 11:16.775
<i>it convinced me to come
to the despair.</i>

11:21.346 --> 11:25.183
<i>I see the pain you've given me
as a gift. Once you give in...</i>

11:32.023 --> 11:33.692
<i>death, rebirth...</i>

11:34.759 --> 11:36.394
<i>giving and taking.</i>

11:37.696 --> 11:38.898
[BOTH GASP]

11:43.701 --> 11:45.303
It will infect us all.

11:56.948 --> 11:58.281
JACOB ON RECORDING: <i>These scars
are testament</i>

11:58.283 --> 11:59.719
<i>to my transformation.</i>

12:32.985 --> 12:35.488
- Honey.
- NICOLE: What?

12:37.389 --> 12:41.025
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah. I'm fine.

12:47.065 --> 12:50.136
- Our new chapter, right?
- Right.

13:16.193 --> 13:17.962
- Ready?
- Mm-hmm.

13:18.230 --> 13:19.298
Nah, hold on.

13:20.131 --> 13:23.867
- Let's do this the right way.
- [NICOLE CHEERS]

13:23.869 --> 13:26.038
There's something to be said
about tradition.

13:31.043 --> 13:32.977
Looks like everything got here
in one piece.

13:34.312 --> 13:36.546
- Where do you want to start?
- I don't know. Tell me,

13:36.548 --> 13:39.382
- where do you want to start?
- Oh, okay, I'm sorry, what were

13:39.384 --> 13:41.352
you just saying to me
about tradition?

13:45.456 --> 13:50.095
<i>♪ Is this for real
Or is this a dream? ♪</i>

13:50.928 --> 13:56.067
<i>♪ I find it hard
Hard to believe ♪</i>

13:58.870 --> 14:02.906
<i>♪ Don't wake me up
Because it feels ♪</i>

14:02.908 --> 14:04.907
♪ Because it feels ♪

14:04.909 --> 14:06.077
[ANDREW SIGHS]

14:07.245 --> 14:09.081
There is so much shit
in that barn.

14:09.815 --> 14:11.150
Like, literal shit?

14:11.850 --> 14:14.519
Yeah, like, literal shit.
Come here.

14:22.561 --> 14:25.331
- So, what do you think?
- Mm...

14:26.532 --> 14:29.100
I definitely think
it's a fixer-upper.

14:31.201 --> 14:32.203
But that's okay.

14:33.938 --> 14:35.908
- I'm used to those.
- Oh!

14:37.308 --> 14:38.943
- Is that so?
- Mm-hmm.

14:40.477 --> 14:41.912
Was I really that bad?

14:42.447 --> 14:45.283
No. Otherwise,
I never would've said "I do."

14:46.985 --> 14:49.520
- Point taken. Ouch.
- [CHUCKLES]

14:51.155 --> 14:53.558
- I'm glad you did.
- Me too.

14:55.426 --> 14:58.194
Stop distracting me.
We got work to do. We got people

14:58.196 --> 15:01.332
- coming over tomorrow.
- Okay, okay, boss.

15:02.466 --> 15:03.634
What time are they coming?

15:03.869 --> 15:06.338
Ben and Michelle said six
and then Ashley...

15:07.639 --> 15:08.673
I don't know.

15:10.442 --> 15:12.144
Don't worry, it's going
to work out, all right.

15:37.469 --> 15:40.239
There's my woman.
How are you doing?

15:41.239 --> 15:42.571
- Good.
- Good?

15:42.573 --> 15:43.675
Good.

15:49.548 --> 15:52.985
[MOANING]

16:11.602 --> 16:13.104
[DOORBELL RINGS]

16:14.239 --> 16:17.209
Swear to God that better be
fucking God.

16:23.313 --> 16:27.517
- Hey.
- Hey! We weren't expecting you

16:27.519 --> 16:30.022
so early. Did you have a friend
drop you off?

16:30.322 --> 16:34.993
- Uh, I took a cab.
- Great, come in.

16:35.559 --> 16:38.195
Sorry about the mess, we were
gonna have everything

16:38.197 --> 16:40.231
all cleared up by the time
everyone got here tomorrow.

16:40.966 --> 16:42.334
It's so good to see you!

16:45.068 --> 16:46.368
Here.

16:46.370 --> 16:49.307
Thank you.
That's very thoughtful of you.

16:50.442 --> 16:52.577
- What is it?
- It's a spider plant.

16:54.546 --> 16:56.081
Native, is it?

16:56.581 --> 16:57.750
I don't know.

16:57.982 --> 16:59.717
I just know they're, like,
impossible to kill.

17:00.418 --> 17:03.552
Low maintenance. Come in,
I'll show you around.

17:03.554 --> 17:05.154
- We can put this away.
- [ASHLEY LAUGH]

17:05.156 --> 17:06.191
Come on!

17:11.329 --> 17:15.465
I'm down to 14 today, I think.

17:16.134 --> 17:19.805
Half are for my anxiety, mixed
with a few anti-depressants,

17:20.038 --> 17:22.406
and the rest are basically
horse tranquilizers...

17:23.374 --> 17:25.275
but still nothing holds a torch

17:25.277 --> 17:27.311
to the shit they were feeding me
in the hospital.

17:27.679 --> 17:29.480
Well, that's progress then,
right?

17:30.013 --> 17:32.049
Yeah, no voices.

17:33.050 --> 17:34.452
- Well, that's good.
- ASHLEY: Yeah...

17:35.286 --> 17:36.355
I think so.

17:37.455 --> 17:39.223
I'm starting to sort
my shit out.

17:40.325 --> 17:44.229
Signed up for school again.
Well, online courses,

17:44.528 --> 17:47.598
and I've been working part time
as a florist.

17:48.165 --> 17:49.835
A florist, really?

17:51.202 --> 17:53.070
I always thought
you hated gardening.

17:53.805 --> 17:58.644
I did. I still do. I'm like
the human version of herbicide.

17:59.644 --> 18:01.277
ASHLEY:
Probably should've consulted

18:01.279 --> 18:03.381
with Ms. Authority here first.

18:04.281 --> 18:08.117
But can't be choosy, I guess.
It's, kind of, hard to get a job

18:08.119 --> 18:10.221
when you have
no real work experience.

18:12.356 --> 18:13.357
ANDREW: Why is that?

18:16.595 --> 18:21.500
Well, after inpatient therapy
I was a bit of a nomad.

18:22.432 --> 18:23.734
Can't really handle people.

18:24.501 --> 18:27.438
They can't really handle me,
thus the plants.

18:30.208 --> 18:33.409
Well, I guess it's kind of hard
to plant your roots

18:33.411 --> 18:35.714
when you're constantly ripping
them out.

18:37.615 --> 18:39.884
Did you really just make
a plant metaphor?

18:40.785 --> 18:42.653
- Yes, I did.
- [NICOLE LAUGHING]

18:43.488 --> 18:46.458
- It was bad.
- Yes, it was.

18:48.492 --> 18:49.861
But, you know, he's not wrong.

18:51.328 --> 18:52.862
NICOLE: It is, it's hard
to start over

18:52.864 --> 18:54.298
when you're a drifter...

18:55.599 --> 18:58.469
to find friends, to find love.

19:00.538 --> 19:03.672
- Marriage and kids?
- NICOLE: Uh-huh.

19:03.674 --> 19:07.311
- Yeah. Let's not go there.
- Not the maternal type?

19:09.280 --> 19:11.682
Like you? No, not really.

19:15.353 --> 19:18.891
Well, I'm just beat, all right?
I'll give you guys

19:19.124 --> 19:21.293
some alone time.
Honey, I love you.

19:23.694 --> 19:24.862
Ashley, it's...

19:28.231 --> 19:29.600
it's always good seeing you.

19:33.270 --> 19:34.373
[LAUGHS]

19:49.854 --> 19:52.757
- NICOLE: Thanks.
- Hey, um...

19:53.791 --> 19:56.494
thank you for reaching out,
you know.

19:58.296 --> 19:59.631
Thanks for giving a shit.

20:00.530 --> 20:02.233
It wasn't the same without you.

20:02.500 --> 20:04.566
I mean, California was great
for Andrew's career

20:04.568 --> 20:05.636
and everything but...

20:06.770 --> 20:08.706
I didn't like that it kept me
from you.

20:10.942 --> 20:12.711
I'm really happy
that you're here.

20:15.713 --> 20:16.714
Me too.

20:24.489 --> 20:25.423
Ah!

20:38.569 --> 20:40.905
NICOLE: Ow! Damn it.

20:41.373 --> 20:43.408
Oh, fuck. That sucks, hold on.

20:48.313 --> 20:49.414
[GASPS]

20:58.690 --> 20:59.991
ASHLEY: Ah, goodnight.

21:17.976 --> 21:20.378
ANDREW: [SIGHS] Honey...

21:20.912 --> 21:24.048
we know it's the same story over
and over again.

21:27.417 --> 21:30.319
It's just that I need you to be
as relaxed as possible,

21:30.321 --> 21:34.892
and Ashley isn't exactly Zen,
if you know what I mean.

21:41.766 --> 21:44.036
Do you know, what I was thinking
about in the car ride?

21:46.704 --> 21:47.605
Tell me.

21:50.374 --> 21:52.009
I want to know my family again.

21:56.981 --> 21:59.750
I still remember when Dad
brought Ben and Ashley home.

22:02.586 --> 22:04.789
Ashley screamed more
than she spoke and...

22:06.357 --> 22:07.591
Ben didn't talk at all.

22:10.595 --> 22:12.631
It took me a really long time
to gain their trust.

22:12.830 --> 22:13.798
Hey.

22:15.532 --> 22:16.533
Hey, you...

22:16.968 --> 22:19.401
you helped them through
a difficult transition.

22:19.403 --> 22:20.705
We helped each other.

22:28.480 --> 22:30.948
We were isolated in California
for so long...

22:31.915 --> 22:34.885
I just worry I'm not gonna be
able to make up for that.

22:35.886 --> 22:37.489
Especially with Ashley.

22:39.790 --> 22:42.360
I am... I want them around.

22:45.997 --> 22:47.699
Come here. Come here.

22:49.032 --> 22:50.468
No one can break you.

22:58.075 --> 23:00.578
- It's in you too.
- It's in you too.

23:14.759 --> 23:15.760
[DOOR CREAKS]

24:22.126 --> 24:25.463
[ASHLEY CRIES]

24:32.971 --> 24:34.005
[SCREAMS]

24:37.974 --> 24:40.211
[ASHLEY SCREAMING]

24:40.811 --> 24:41.812
Ash!

24:42.913 --> 24:44.081
Ashley!

24:46.617 --> 24:47.618
Ashley!

24:50.121 --> 24:51.122
Ash!

24:52.490 --> 24:54.859
- Ashley, where are you?
- [ASHLEY CRYING]

24:56.493 --> 24:57.495
Ashley!

24:58.461 --> 24:59.931
Okay, hold on, hold on, hold on.

25:07.805 --> 25:10.041
NICOLE: [PANTS] Ash?

25:12.109 --> 25:13.110
Ashley?

25:14.945 --> 25:16.714
<i>Ashley, are you down here?</i>

25:17.882 --> 25:19.217
<i>Ashley?</i>

25:20.718 --> 25:22.621
- [ASHLEY CRYING]
- Ash!

25:23.520 --> 25:26.689
Ashley, oh, my God!
Are you okay? What's wrong?

25:26.691 --> 25:28.757
- [GROANS]
- Ashley! Are you okay?

25:28.759 --> 25:30.758
Tell me what's wrong. Ashley?

25:30.760 --> 25:31.863
Ashley, is someone in the house?

25:32.063 --> 25:35.663
Back off. It's okay,
you're home. You're okay.

25:35.665 --> 25:37.665
You're okay. You're okay,
Ashley.

25:37.667 --> 25:41.104
Ashley, Look at me. Ashley!

25:42.006 --> 25:45.977
- [ASHLEY CRIES]
- Ash. Ash. Ashley.

26:08.665 --> 26:10.335
BEN: I thought Californians
were early risers.

26:12.269 --> 26:14.003
Yeah, we figured, we'd take
notes from your Hawks

26:14.005 --> 26:16.775
- and sleep in this season.
- Oh, shit.

26:18.276 --> 26:20.843
I come bearing gifts,
and this is how you treat me?

26:20.845 --> 26:24.249
- Yeah. Good to see you.
- Nice to see you.

26:27.017 --> 26:29.019
- Did she see me pull up?
- No, I don't think so.

26:31.056 --> 26:33.057
- Man, the chair looks great.
- Thanks.

26:41.599 --> 26:44.732
Ben? Oh, my God,
what are you doing here?

26:44.734 --> 26:47.636
- ANDREW: Ah, fuck!
- BEN: Surprise.

26:47.638 --> 26:49.139
NICOLE: Ouch! Honey,
are you all right?

26:49.874 --> 26:52.110
Yeah, I think I caught it
on a staple or something.

26:52.609 --> 26:54.878
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'll live.

26:59.217 --> 27:01.119
It is so great to have
you back home, Nicki.

27:01.586 --> 27:02.988
It's really great to be home.

27:06.891 --> 27:09.227
- Dad's old chair.
- Mm-hmm.

27:13.597 --> 27:15.099
Oh, come on. Keep it together.

27:16.835 --> 27:18.336
I was just trying to do
something nice.

27:20.938 --> 27:22.974
No, Ben, it's really,
really sweet.

27:24.275 --> 27:26.944
I was just looking at pictures
of us on this thing,

27:27.344 --> 27:28.846
when we were younger and...

27:30.647 --> 27:33.382
I can't believe you hung onto it
for me. Thank you.

27:33.384 --> 27:35.385
Every child should have
an heirloom, I guess.

27:35.853 --> 27:38.722
[LAUGHS] Yeah.
What'd you keep?

27:39.757 --> 27:40.825
The adoption record.

27:42.393 --> 27:44.129
Framed it and hung it
in my office.

27:45.696 --> 27:46.798
That's really nice.

27:48.031 --> 27:49.299
BEN: Uh, Where would you
like this?

27:49.932 --> 27:51.001
NICOLE: Oh, um...

27:53.170 --> 27:55.840
- [NICOLE CLEARS THROAT]
- Oh, wow! Look at that view.

27:56.272 --> 27:59.174
Yeah, sure beats looking
at your neighbors' building.

27:59.176 --> 28:02.246
Which is what we did a lot
of in California.

28:03.212 --> 28:05.316
- This is nice.
- I like it.

28:07.184 --> 28:09.354
You can just set that here.
Right there.

28:11.923 --> 28:14.024
BEN: [EXHALES] The house
is coming together nicely.

28:14.424 --> 28:17.428
Yeah. Slowly but surely.

28:19.163 --> 28:20.464
First night in the new place?

28:21.699 --> 28:23.935
No, it's not that. Um...

28:25.368 --> 28:27.137
Ashley came in last night.

28:28.038 --> 28:29.874
That's great! Where's she at?

28:30.340 --> 28:34.745
She's still sleeping. She, um,
sort of had an episode.

28:35.380 --> 28:37.481
Yeah, she was screaming
bloody murder in the basement.

28:37.714 --> 28:39.750
She had a night terror.

28:40.785 --> 28:42.153
NICOLE: It was bad, Ben.

28:42.452 --> 28:44.388
I haven't seen her like that
even as a kid.

28:45.890 --> 28:49.326
It was different like more...
more real.

28:51.127 --> 28:52.797
I thought you said
she was improving.

28:54.999 --> 28:56.800
Yeah, she was.

28:59.135 --> 29:01.038
Uh, I'm going to head out.

29:01.372 --> 29:02.939
I'll talk to you guys later
tonight.

29:02.941 --> 29:05.207
NICOLE: Ben, Ben, come on.
Just stay for a little bit.

29:05.209 --> 29:07.412
- ANDREW: Come on, dude, stay.
- No, I can't.

29:08.211 --> 29:09.413
We'll talk more tonight.

29:10.815 --> 29:11.816
Ben.

29:14.718 --> 29:15.519
That was weird.

29:17.354 --> 29:20.024
- Hope he's okay.
- NICOLE: Yeah.

29:58.962 --> 29:59.963
Morning.

30:01.832 --> 30:02.834
It's 3 p.m.

30:15.145 --> 30:16.547
ASHLEY: Where's Nicole?

30:17.047 --> 30:18.583
ANDREW: Making up
for lost sleep.

30:24.555 --> 30:26.524
She didn't need to stay up
with me.

30:29.093 --> 30:30.094
Seriously?

30:31.295 --> 30:33.898
Didn't you and Ben coin
the phrase Mama-Sis?

30:34.464 --> 30:37.166
Touché. She always
hated it, though.

30:37.534 --> 30:39.903
Said it sounded like incest.

30:45.041 --> 30:46.276
It was a panic attack.

30:49.212 --> 30:51.382
- What?
- In the basement.

30:53.150 --> 30:55.586
I'll bet your friends
in the psych ward loved that.

30:58.221 --> 31:01.489
Sorry, I didn't mean to upset
anyone.

31:01.491 --> 31:03.357
Then I guess
you're not responsible, then.

31:03.359 --> 31:05.295
I mean, look you know
what she's been through.

31:12.936 --> 31:13.937
Ash.

31:16.106 --> 31:17.474
Just be present for Nicole...

31:20.344 --> 31:22.547
or leave before you cause
any more damage.

31:29.987 --> 31:31.122
Not a problem.

31:38.327 --> 31:41.633
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

32:32.215 --> 32:34.318
[DOOR OPENS]

33:08.085 --> 33:09.286
Do you need something?

33:09.720 --> 33:13.321
Um, no. I just... I wanted
to know if you were okay.

33:13.323 --> 33:14.325
I'm fine, thanks.

33:19.230 --> 33:20.230
Ashley!

33:21.566 --> 33:22.733
Ashley, wait!

33:25.501 --> 33:26.736
NICOLE: Where are you going?

33:27.637 --> 33:30.538
Ashley, just talk to me
for a minute, please!

33:30.540 --> 33:31.775
ASHLEY: I made a mistake.

33:32.509 --> 33:34.011
NICOLE: What are you talking
about?

33:35.311 --> 33:38.014
- I'm not ready for this.
- Who is really

33:38.383 --> 33:40.117
ready for anything
in their life?

33:43.054 --> 33:44.721
I'm trying to create something
here...

33:45.655 --> 33:48.058
something that we haven't had
since Dad died.

33:50.193 --> 33:54.531
Please, I'm doing everybody
a favor, trust me.

33:55.232 --> 33:58.702
No, you trust me.
You are a part of this.

34:01.506 --> 34:04.542
- I used to be.
- Just stay the night.

34:05.509 --> 34:07.110
We'll start fresh
in the morning.

34:07.510 --> 34:10.815
Andrew and I really...
Ashley, Ashley,

34:11.047 --> 34:12.649
just stay until the end
of dinner, that okay?

34:14.184 --> 34:16.018
Ben is going to be crushed
if he doesn't see you.

34:17.085 --> 34:19.621
And then afterwards, if you still
feel like you want to leave,

34:19.623 --> 34:21.324
I'll take you anywhere you want
to go.

34:28.565 --> 34:30.266
MICHELLE: G... Graham.

34:31.134 --> 34:36.204
Yes. Okay, okay. Gr... Yeah,
I know. I know, Graham!

34:36.206 --> 34:38.708
Will you just stop interrupting
me for like a second?

34:39.742 --> 34:43.545
When I say that I need
to decompress, thank me

34:43.547 --> 34:45.282
in advance for sparing
your life.

34:45.583 --> 34:47.614
Oh, okay. Yeah, sure try
your little power play,

34:47.617 --> 34:51.119
see what happens. Huh? Let me
tell you something, Graham.

34:51.121 --> 34:53.253
I've got two Masters,
a loaded 9mil,

34:53.255 --> 34:55.824
and perfect 34B's, any of which
that could turn you

34:55.826 --> 34:57.293
and your prick inside out.

34:57.295 --> 34:59.597
So, let's just say it together,
huh? Competence!

35:01.766 --> 35:02.800
Jesus Christ.

35:06.269 --> 35:08.269
Did you just threaten
to smoke your partner?

35:08.271 --> 35:10.206
No, just a memo between friends.

35:11.340 --> 35:13.777
- I'm glad we're not friends.
- Oh, no, I like you,

35:14.177 --> 35:16.179
just Graham,
on the other hand...

35:18.548 --> 35:20.650
- Maybe, it's time to leave.
- Leave?

35:21.152 --> 35:24.485
No, leaving solves nothing,
honey, tenacity wins.

35:24.487 --> 35:27.155
We don't need tenacity
right now, we need a break.

35:27.157 --> 35:28.557
A break? Okay, you know,

35:28.559 --> 35:30.724
I don't think he's going to be
calling anytime soon.

35:30.726 --> 35:32.797
- I think, he got the point.
- Good.

35:33.597 --> 35:34.731
Because it'd just be really nice

35:34.898 --> 35:36.666
if you weren't glued
to your phone all weekend.

35:37.300 --> 35:38.768
Monday through Friday
is bad enough.

35:39.402 --> 35:40.669
Yikes!

35:41.371 --> 35:43.407
- [ZIPPER ZIPS]
- Take a chill pill.

35:47.878 --> 35:49.447
You know, I didn't mean it
like that.

35:50.114 --> 35:52.150
It's fine. Just drop it.

35:53.282 --> 35:54.451
You know what, no.

35:54.652 --> 35:57.186
Just because Ashley
is struggling with some shit,

35:57.188 --> 35:58.556
doesn't mean you have to too.

36:03.628 --> 36:07.298
- [SIGHS] Yeah, you're right.
- Damn straight, I'm right.

36:07.898 --> 36:11.469
It took a little bit of time
but you turned out okay.

36:12.702 --> 36:13.704
I'm proud of you.

36:15.338 --> 36:17.207
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

36:17.907 --> 36:20.242
Can you just turn off
this emo attitude?

36:20.244 --> 36:21.946
You're a lot stronger
than you realize.

36:22.579 --> 36:24.244
You know, just help her through
this shit

36:24.246 --> 36:26.384
and show her how it's done.

36:37.360 --> 36:38.360
Hey.

36:39.295 --> 36:42.599
- This look okay?
- Yeah, you look great, hun.

36:47.503 --> 36:49.339
You're not her guardian angel,
you know.

36:51.442 --> 36:52.476
She's a grown woman now,

36:52.643 --> 36:54.244
she should be able to take care
of herself.

36:55.413 --> 36:57.380
But she can't take care
of herself.

36:58.782 --> 37:01.685
- Why can't you accept that?
- I did...

37:03.387 --> 37:04.488
years ago.

37:06.789 --> 37:08.992
They should've never released
her from the hospital.

37:09.726 --> 37:12.896
She obviously needs a lot
of supervision and help.

37:14.697 --> 37:16.299
How can you be so cold to her?

37:17.668 --> 37:20.003
Honestly, what has she
ever done to you, really?

37:20.237 --> 37:21.568
Nothing, it's just

37:21.570 --> 37:23.505
that she's bringing you down
and it's pissing me off.

37:23.507 --> 37:24.840
Well, you have
a really shitty way

37:24.842 --> 37:26.911
of showing your concern
for my well-being.

37:28.711 --> 37:30.577
I just... I don't know why

37:30.579 --> 37:32.514
you didn't let her go
when she wanted to leave.

37:32.516 --> 37:33.918
Because she's my sister.

37:34.684 --> 37:36.820
- She's not your sister.
- BEN: <i>Hello?</i>

37:37.954 --> 37:40.490
- <i>Where is everyone?</i>
- MICHELLE: <i>Hello?</i>

37:41.925 --> 37:43.994
- <i>Andrew?</i>
- ANDREW: <i>Hey.</i>

38:45.989 --> 38:48.958
- You look good, Ash.
- [SCOFFS] Whatever.

38:50.393 --> 38:52.063
You look happy.

38:54.297 --> 38:57.334
I'm trying. One day at a time,
you know?

38:59.969 --> 39:04.674
[JEREMY MIMICKING HOWL]

39:05.708 --> 39:08.078
Andy, get your ass out here!

39:10.780 --> 39:12.516
Ah, there he is!

39:13.550 --> 39:16.086
- [GRUNTS] Here I come.
- ANDREW: All right!

39:16.485 --> 39:22.025
[GRUNTS] Here I come. Howl
with me!

39:22.425 --> 39:26.897
Brother, I will make you howl.
[MIMICKING HOWL]

39:27.563 --> 39:31.367
Jesus, it's been years, man!
How the hell have you been?

39:31.635 --> 39:34.004
I'm good. I've been good.

39:34.737 --> 39:36.604
Hey, I thought you said,
you were going to bring someone.

39:36.606 --> 39:39.476
Oh, yeah, yeah, Kim. She'll be
around, her shift ends at eight.

39:39.842 --> 39:41.510
Ah, come on! Who cares?

39:41.710 --> 39:44.746
Great, great. Come inside, man.
I got food on the way. It's...

39:44.748 --> 39:47.684
Food? Jeremy need drink.

39:48.652 --> 39:50.721
A drink! A pint!

39:50.920 --> 39:55.458
A pint for brother Jeremy!
A pint for brother Andrew!

39:56.559 --> 39:58.795
I don't know who this man
is anymore.

39:59.829 --> 40:04.400
Andrew, the guy who once drank
an entire bottle of tequila

40:04.601 --> 40:07.438
and tried to fight
a rugby team...

40:07.938 --> 40:12.175
now wears Mr. Rogers sweaters
and drinks grape juice. Huh!

40:12.610 --> 40:16.179
I'm sorry that my taste is
too sophisticated for even you.

40:16.579 --> 40:19.549
Tell me, did Nicole pluck
your berries...

40:20.016 --> 40:22.650
or did they just shrivel up
and fall off the vine?

40:22.652 --> 40:24.954
Okay, you know, my berries
are just fine, okay?

40:25.422 --> 40:27.021
JEREMY: [LAUGHS] Yeah,
says the guy

40:27.023 --> 40:30.124
who built his fucking wine rack
before his love shack.

40:30.126 --> 40:31.626
Oh, you know what, fuck off!

40:31.628 --> 40:33.864
- You uncivilized savage.
- JEREMY: Oh!

40:53.516 --> 40:55.950
I knew California would make
you soft.

40:55.952 --> 40:57.952
Of course it would. All it is
a bunch

40:57.954 --> 40:59.890
of fucking famous people
and kale.

41:00.123 --> 41:04.193
And the ocean, and fresh fruit,
the sun.

41:04.994 --> 41:07.798
And you traded all that
for the winters of Siberia?

41:10.668 --> 41:12.135
Family is worth freezing for.

41:15.873 --> 41:16.874
Sure is.

41:21.110 --> 41:22.112
This one's nice.

41:23.913 --> 41:24.914
NICOLE: Oh, yeah.

41:26.650 --> 41:27.651
Yeah.

41:28.518 --> 41:31.187
This was taken the day that Dad
brought you and Ben home.

41:31.588 --> 41:32.890
Do you remember that?

41:35.525 --> 41:36.527
Just like yesterday.

41:39.963 --> 41:42.066
Welcome back, Nicole and Andrew.

41:43.000 --> 41:44.501
Bring on the bubbly!

41:45.601 --> 41:47.170
Please. Thank you.

41:51.240 --> 41:52.242
Oh, uh...

41:53.576 --> 41:54.677
I shouldn't.

41:55.112 --> 41:57.681
Come on, Mama-Sis,
one's not going to kill you.

42:02.152 --> 42:04.288
No fucking way!

42:05.222 --> 42:06.757
Wait, I don't get it.

42:07.958 --> 42:11.929
- I'm pregnant.
- Yes! Oh, my God!

42:12.128 --> 42:14.963
BEN: Oh!

42:14.965 --> 42:17.264
JEREMY: Looks like the berries
are hanging just fine

42:17.266 --> 42:20.703
- after all, huh?
- Congratulations.

42:22.739 --> 42:25.608
- Hey, now it's a celebration.
- Congrats to you two.

42:27.677 --> 42:29.610
- [LAUGHTER]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

42:29.612 --> 42:31.080
[HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]

42:33.849 --> 42:36.853
[INAUDIBLE]

42:43.793 --> 42:46.763
[DISTANT VOICE] Ashley?
Aren't you excited?

42:48.565 --> 42:51.302
- Ashley?
- [RINGING CONTINUES]

43:06.081 --> 43:07.083
What?

43:07.684 --> 43:10.153
You're going to be an aunt,
aren't you excited?

43:12.322 --> 43:14.291
Yeah, sure.

43:27.603 --> 43:28.605
You just...

43:29.271 --> 43:32.610
- can't be happy for her?
- Just let it go, okay?

43:34.077 --> 43:37.247
- Andy...
- No! I'm interested.

43:39.215 --> 43:40.217
I'm interested.

43:41.150 --> 43:43.952
Is there any particular reason
why you deem it

43:43.954 --> 43:47.222
necessary to, yet again,
suck the fucking happiness

43:47.224 --> 43:48.925
out of the fucking room?

43:49.192 --> 43:52.262
I guess we opened that bottle
of champagne a little too early.

43:52.661 --> 43:55.762
- BEN: Hey, Andrew, relax, man.
- No, no, she's done nothing

43:55.764 --> 43:59.700
but scare my wife, my wife,
ever since she got here.

43:59.702 --> 44:01.371
You know what, Andrew,
I am perfectly capable

44:01.605 --> 44:03.005
of speaking for myself,

44:03.206 --> 44:06.175
and that being said,
you're acting like an asshole.

44:07.911 --> 44:10.110
I guess, I don't know what
the fuck I'm talking about then,

44:10.112 --> 44:11.080
huh?

44:12.282 --> 44:14.050
ASHLEY: She came out in pieces.

44:16.619 --> 44:17.421
What?

44:19.389 --> 44:20.691
Eighteen months ago...

44:23.793 --> 44:29.098
I was so weak that my doctors
urged me to terminate her.

44:32.068 --> 44:34.838
They said she'd most likely come
all fucked up...

44:37.873 --> 44:40.243
with holes in her brain
or something worse.

44:43.213 --> 44:47.985
I was in a constant state
of insomnia and paranoia so...

44:49.318 --> 44:50.454
I trusted them.

44:54.923 --> 44:58.728
I can still feel the cold steel
as they pried me open...

45:01.931 --> 45:06.235
And smell the stench that filled
the room as...

45:07.269 --> 45:09.940
they blended her up inside me...

45:10.840 --> 45:12.342
and vacuumed her out...

45:13.409 --> 45:14.411
like trash.

45:30.927 --> 45:32.929
Still want me to plan
the baby shower?

45:38.001 --> 45:39.236
You're fucking pathetic.

45:53.349 --> 45:55.384
NICOLE: <i>Why would she say
something like that?</i>

45:56.385 --> 45:58.221
Do you think that's the truth?

45:58.922 --> 46:00.791
Do you think it was too much
too soon?

46:01.925 --> 46:04.228
- She's not used to crowds.
- Or frat boys.

46:06.061 --> 46:07.063
I know.

46:08.398 --> 46:12.035
This whole night. God, I wish
I could drink.

46:13.369 --> 46:15.270
<i>Un momento.</i>

46:16.505 --> 46:21.777
I think, I saw something in...
Uh, aha! Baby safe.

46:22.411 --> 46:24.980
You guys, this is still
a celebration, right?

46:25.748 --> 46:29.452
Babe, babe, you're going to be
an uncle. Yup.

46:31.054 --> 46:33.389
The three of us can still
salvage the night, right?

46:34.523 --> 46:37.460
Can you please take a moment
and celebrate with your sister?

46:38.994 --> 46:40.262
You two start without me.

46:40.797 --> 46:42.496
I just need to clear my head
for a bit.

46:42.498 --> 46:44.865
All right, you're not leaving
until you have this toast

46:44.867 --> 46:45.802
with us.

46:47.003 --> 46:50.340
So, beautiful. Thought
of any names yet?

46:50.907 --> 46:52.542
You know, it's...
it's still early.

46:52.976 --> 46:54.374
We don't want to get ahead
of ourselves.

46:54.376 --> 46:58.079
Okay. Bitch, you're glowing,
all right? Just relax.

46:58.081 --> 46:59.313
MICHELLE: You're going
to be fine.

46:59.315 --> 47:01.885
- Come on, what do you've got?
- Okay, um...

47:03.318 --> 47:06.822
if it's a boy, Andrew wants
to name him Oliver,

47:07.123 --> 47:10.059
after his father,
and if it's a girl...

47:10.561 --> 47:13.427
- I've chosen Savannah.
- Savannah?

47:13.429 --> 47:18.134
Oh, my God, that's so hot.
Guaranteed to be a pretty one.

47:22.938 --> 47:25.942
- To family!
- BEN AND NICOLE: To family.

47:34.983 --> 47:37.221
I'm sorry. I need
to get some air.

47:39.422 --> 47:40.423
Oh.

47:48.530 --> 47:49.532
Congratulations.

47:54.469 --> 47:55.471
Ben...

47:58.007 --> 47:59.443
she'll be okay, right?

48:13.023 --> 48:14.557
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

48:35.545 --> 48:37.047
I would've been there, Ash.

48:38.380 --> 48:39.949
ASHLEY: I highly doubt that.

48:41.117 --> 48:42.416
BEN: I went
to the psych evaluations

48:42.418 --> 48:45.421
with you. The late night
emergency room visits?

48:46.155 --> 48:47.557
ASHLEY: And thought I was crazy.

48:49.224 --> 48:50.460
You were hurting yourself.

48:55.331 --> 48:56.599
Does this look familiar...

48:57.534 --> 48:58.535
to you?

48:59.135 --> 49:03.940
- Mom and Dad? Jacob Murphy?
- Stop this, Ash. Please.

49:04.340 --> 49:06.242
You know what this is.

49:06.543 --> 49:10.012
- You saw it that night.
- I saw Mom and Dad.

49:11.181 --> 49:13.581
I saw that maniac slit
his own throat.

49:13.583 --> 49:16.316
There was something else
in the house.

49:16.318 --> 49:19.387
Jacob Murphy has been dead
for 20 years.

49:19.389 --> 49:24.059
It didn't end with Murphy.
Okay, he was just a body.

49:24.061 --> 49:27.564
He... he was just a vessel.
One of many.

49:27.963 --> 49:29.465
Do you hear what you are saying?

49:34.336 --> 49:36.605
I wanted to keep my baby, Ben.

49:38.208 --> 49:43.746
But I had to save her from him.
Not a man who died 20 years ago.

49:44.313 --> 49:46.016
You have to deal with your shit.

49:49.552 --> 49:51.153
You decided that child's life.

49:52.956 --> 49:57.728
It threatened to cut her out
of me every time I slept.

49:59.996 --> 50:01.329
Have you been taking your pills?

50:01.331 --> 50:05.666
They make everything cloudy.
I can't function!

